description:
What impact do you have on those around you? Often, we attribute more value to those actions that require more effort from us; however, thats not always the case. Sometimes its the little things that have the most impact.

Ceri Johnson, one of our much-loved girls' deans, shares her purpose and the journey that led her from being a student to a girls' dean at Fountainview Academy.

Students from all over the world are attracted to Fountainview because of its balanced approach to education. Each staff member is personally committed to the eternal success of every student, and together they strive for the highest standards in every respect.
